<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-81] The options set inside the makefault mediator not set properly when a fault occurs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-81</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Created the following sequence and tried to validate against an invalid xsd. Since the validation fails, a saop fault should be returned.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;definitions xmlns=&quot;http://ws.apache.org/ns/synapse&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;localEntry key=&quot;filter_validate_schema&quot;  src=&quot;file:repository/conf/sample/resources/validate/div_schema.xsd&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;validate&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;schema key=&quot;filter_validate_schema&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;on-fail&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                    &amp;lt;makefault trace=&quot;enable&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                        &amp;lt;code value=&quot;tns:Receiver&quot; xmlns:tns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                        &amp;lt;reason value=&quot;Invalid custom quote request&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;detail value=&quot;Detailed description of the soap fault&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                    &amp;lt;/makefault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                    &amp;lt;send/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;/on-fail&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/validate&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;address  uri=&quot;http://localhost:9001/axis2/services/Division&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/send&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/in&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;log level=&quot;full&quot; separator=&quot;,&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;property name=&quot;after_filt_prop&quot; value=&quot;Incoming Message getting filtered -  After&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/log&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;send/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/out&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/definitions&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When checked the synapse console, I realized that the soap fault which is created is blank.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&apos;1.0&apos; encoding=&apos;utf-8&apos;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv=&quot;http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;soapenv:Body&amp;gt;	&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;faultcode&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;/faultcode&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;faultstring&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;/faultstring&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;detail&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
				&amp;lt;/detail&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
			&amp;lt;/soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/soapenv:Envelope&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP, j2sdk1.4.2_13</environment>
